  "text": "Human papilloma virus Polymerase chain reaction for HPV was performed using general primers MY09 and MY11 and GP5 þ /GP6 þ [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Validation of the DNA quality and the efficacy of the PCR were carried out with PCR for the housekeeping gene GAPDH. Immunohistochemistry for p16 INK4A was performed on formalinfixed paraffin-embedded tissue slides pre-treated in DAKO PT Link, incubated with P16 (JC8) antibody, Santa Cruz (Santa Cruz Biiotechnology Inc., Santa Cruz, CA, USA), and visualised using DAKO Envision Flex þ system. Slides were evaluated by a pathologist as positive, if there was a strong diffuse staining of more than 50% of the tumour cells.",
